question.text: Ribulose biphosphate carboxylase oxygenase (RuBisCO) enzyme catalyses the reaction between

options.text: Oxaloacetic acid and acetyl  <math><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">A</mi></math>

solution.text: Ribulose biphosphate carboxylase oxygenase  <math><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">R</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">u</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">B</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mo>)</mo></math>  is the most abundant protein of the plant world. This is an important protein which is an enzyme playing a significant role in Calvin cycle. This enzyme catalyzes the reaction of  <math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>  (1C) with 1,5-RUBP (5C) to form an unstable 6C compound which then forms 2 3C compounds - Phosphoglyceric acid by hydrolysis.
